pubmed_race_df <- read_tsv('data/pubmed/authors.tsv.xz') %>%
  filter(reverse_position == 1) %>%
  left_join(read_tsv('data/pubmed/articles.tsv.xz'), by = 'pmid') %>%
  mutate(year = substr(publication_date, 1, 4) %>% ymd(truncated = 2)) %>%
  rename('surname' = last_name) %>% 
  predict_race(surname.only = T, impute.missing = F) %>%
  mutate(publication_date = ymd(publication_date, truncated = 2))

Descriptive statistics

Prepare data frames for later analyses:

  • rbind results of race predictions in ISMB and Pubmed
  • pivot long
  • compute mean, sd, marginal error
  • add “White” vs. “Others”
ismb_pubmed <- ismb_race_df %>%
  select(year, contains('pred')) %>%
  mutate(publication_date = year,
         type = 'ISMB',
         journal = 'ISMB',
         pred_sum_others = pred.his + pred.oth + pred.bla) %>%
  rbind(
    pubmed_race_df %>%
      select(year, journal, publication_date, contains('pred')) %>%
      mutate(type = 'Pubmed',
             pred_sum_others = pred.his + pred.oth + pred.bla)
  ) %>%
  pivot_longer(contains('pred'),
               names_to = 'Race',
               values_to = 'Probabilities') %>%
  recode_race() %>%
  group_by(type, year, publication_date, Race) %>%
  add_count() %>%
  mutate(
    mean_prob = mean(Probabilities, na.rm = T),
    sd_prob = sd(Probabilities, na.rm = T),
    n = mean(n),
    me_prob = alpha * sd_prob / sqrt(n)
  ) %>%
  ungroup()

Stacked bar plots:

plot_dynamic_race <- vector('list', length = n_jours)
i <- 0
for (jour in my_jours){
  i <- i + 1
  plot_dynamic_race[[i]] <- ismb_pubmed %>%
    filter(type == 'Pubmed' & journal == jour & (Race != 'All others')) %>%
    group_by(year, Race) %>%
    summarise(mean_prob = mean(Probabilities, na.rm = T)) %>%
    ungroup() %>% 
    dynamic_contribution(jour)
}

do.call(cowplot::plot_grid, c(plot_dynamic_race, nrow = 3))

ismb_pubmed %>%
  filter(type == 'ISMB' & (Race != 'All others')) %>% 
  group_by(year, Race) %>%
  summarise(mean_prob = mean(Probabilities, na.rm = T)) %>%
  dynamic_contribution('ISMB keynote speakers')

# boxplot ismb, pubmed faceted by year
ismb_pubmed %>% 
  filter(Race == 'White') %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = type, fill = type, y = Probabilities)) +
  geom_violin(alpha = 0.8) +
  facet_wrap(~ year(year), nrow = 3) +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(x = NULL, y = 'Probabilities of being white') +

Confidence interval of the mean? (Aggregation)

Null: The proportion of white keynote ISMB speakers is not larger the proportions of white last authors published in Pubmed Central. Alternative: The proportion of white keynote ISMB speakers is larger the proportions of white last authors published in Pubmed Central. How do we take time component into account? Right now, I’m thinking we can use year as a random variable. Perhaps we should allow for random slope as well?

Bootstrap?

get_summary <- function(df){
  df %>% filter(type == 'ISMB') %>% select(- Probabilities) %>% distinct()
}

ggplot(ismb_pubmed %>% filter(Race == 'White' | Race == 'Asian' | Race == 'All others'),
       aes(x = year)) +
  facet_grid(cols = vars(fct_rev(Race))) +
  geom_smooth(aes(x = publication_date, y = Probabilities, color = type, fill = type)) +
  geom_point(
    data = . %>% filter(type == 'ISMB'),
    aes(y = Probabilities, color = type),
    alpha = 0.2,
    show.legend = F
  ) +
  geom_point(
    data = . %>% get_summary(),
    aes(y = mean_prob, color = type),
    shape = 2,
    alpha = 0.5,
    show.legend = F
  ) +
  geom_linerange(
    data = . %>% get_summary(),
    aes(
      ymin = mean_prob - me_prob,
      ymax = mean_prob + me_prob,
      color = type
    ),
    alpha = 0.5,
    show.legend = F
  ) +
  theme_bw() +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 1, 0.2)) +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank()) +
  scale_color_viridis_d(option = 'E') +
  scale_fill_viridis_d(option = 'E') +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0, 1)) +
  labs(x = NULL)
